ZH: 她的压力很大，需要好好休息。
EN: She is under a lot of pressure and needs to rest well.

ZH: 这个箱子太重了，我提不起来。
EN: This box is too heavy for me to lift.

ZH: 考试是对学生的一种压力。
EN: Exams are a form of pressure on students.

ZH: 这个按钮要按得很重才能开启。
EN: You have to press this button hard to open it.

ZH: 她的手指被门夹住，疼得厉害。
EN: Her finger got caught in the door and it hurts badly.

ZH: 这个房间的气压很低，需要打开窗户通风。
EN: The air pressure in this room is low, we need to open the windows for ventilation.

ZH: 这块布很厚，压在身上很暖和。
EN: This piece of cloth is thick, it feels warm when pressed against the body.

ZH: 常常坐着不动容易对腿部造成压力。
EN: Sitting still for long periods can put pressure on your legs.

ZH: 让我帮你按摩一下，可以减轻肩膀上的压力。
EN: Let me give you a massage to relieve the pressure on your shoulders.

ZH: 长时间的用眼过度容易导致眼压升高。
EN: Prolonged excessive use of eyes can lead to increased eye pressure.

ZH: 水压突然增大，导致水管爆裂。
EN: The sudden increase in water pressure caused the pipe to burst.

ZH: 运动可以缓解工作带来的紧张压力。
EN: Exercise can help relieve the tension and pressure from work.

ZH: 假期是释放压力的好时机。
EN: Holidays are a great time to release stress.

ZH: 这个板块承受不了那么大的压力。
EN: This plate cannot withstand such great pressure.

ZH: 他常常对自己有很高的期望，压力很大。
EN: He often has high expectations for himself, which creates a lot of pressure.

ZH: 这份工作的压力很大，需要有很强的心理承受能力。
EN: This job has a lot of pressure and requires strong mental resilience.

ZH: 长时间低头看手机容易给颈椎带来压力。
EN: Bending down to look at your phone for a long time can put pressure on your neck.

ZH: 睡眠不足容易让人感到整晚都在被压着。
EN: Lack of sleep can make a person feel as if they are being pressed down all night.

ZH: 她被车子压倒了，需要紧急送医院。
EN: She was run over by a car and needs to be rushed to the hospital.

ZH: 她在工作中被朋友压制得很紧。
EN: She feels oppressed by her friends at work.
